## packages/svelte/tests/README.md:7-11
7: - `compiler` options are different currently, a wrapper function in `helpers.js` was added and call sites rerouted to that
8: - regex in the loader was adjusted, a `$` was added to the `import * as ..` regex (because the new runtime does `import * as $ from ..` for the runtime)
9: - `vitest.config.js` was altered: `resolve-svelte` plugin also aliases `svelte` (the current runtime import) and `test.dir` was adjusted because the monorepo structure is different (compiler/runtime are separate packages here currently)
10: - new runtime does not expose things like raf etc, which were used in some tests (runtime for example; for transition/animation tests). These are commented out for now
11: - when changing an attribute, the JSDOM does not reflect the value immediately anymore because the runtime does update the DOM in after a tick, not synchronously - this results in many tests needing additional `await Promise.resolve()` lines

